==Views==
Weston promotes the [[white genocide conspiracy theory]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Anti-Muslim prejudice ‘is moving to the mainstream’ |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/dec/05/far-right-muslim-cultural-civil-war|author=Mark Townsend |publisher= |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=5 December 2015}}</ref> He claimed white genocide is occurring in Britain,<ref>{{cite news|title=Paul Westion: Preventing White Genocide|author=Paul Weston |url=https://libertygb.org.uk/news/paul-weston-preventing-white-genocide|website=Liberty GB |publisher=[[Liberty GB]] |date=24 November 2013}}</ref> and has used the [[United Nations]] definition of genocide as proof of its existence.<ref>{{cite news|title=Exposed: "White Genocide" Claims of Top UKIP Figure |url=https://www.hopenothate.org.uk/2017/03/14/exposed-white-genocide-claims-top-ukip-figure/|author=David Lawrence |publisher=[[Hope Not Hate]] |date=14 March 2017}}</ref>

